# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
*.egg
dist/
build/
*.so

# Virtual environments. env/ is anchored to root — the bare pattern wrongly
# matched project dirs named env (workspace/nodesets/env/, the env doc pages),
# silently dropping them from `git add -A` in a fresh clone of the public repo.
.venv/
venv/
/env/

# Data and model artifacts — root data/ only (datasets, checkpoints, scene
# assets). Anchored so it does NOT match project dirs named data
# (scripts/data/, .claude/commands/*/data/, docs/pages/aas/mirror/*/data/),
# which made the bare pattern need a growing list of `!` exceptions.
/data/
*.pth
*.ckpt
# Large model checkpoints that live beside the backend (orbax/JAX format —
# ocdbt + sharded blobs, not *.pth/*.ckpt). ~12G, never tracked. (Previously
# covered by the bare `data/` rule before it was anchored to `/data/`.)
agentcanvas/backend/data/

# Outputs — only outputs/archive/ is tracked. Everything else (canvas
# runs, eval runs, architect design history, loose files) is local-only.
# Curate to outputs/archive/{slug}-YYYY-MM-DD/ if any run is worth
# preserving for reproducibility.
outputs/*
!outputs/archive/
multirun/

# IDE
.idea/
# Per-user editor config — local-only, never tracked.
**/.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# OMC runtime state (regenerated by the OMC tool; keep out of git)
.omc/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log
wandb/

# Generic process-bookkeeping artefacts that may appear elsewhere too.
# (outputs/design_runs/ is fully ignored above, so its *.pid / backend.log /
# smoke_log.jsonl / etc don't need separate rules anymore.)
*.pid
*.pgid

# Generated launcher scripts (created by install.sh)
agentcanvas/launch.sh

# Node (agentcanvas frontend)
node_modules/

# Environment files
.env
*.env.local
# Build artifacts
*.tsbuildinfo
.vite/

# Reference repos (raw files, not submodules) — entire dir, never tracked
third_party/zz_just_for_refer/

# Upstream clones fetched on-demand by workspace/nodesets/_upstream/*/fetch_upstream.sh
workspace/nodesets/_upstream/*/upstream/

# Install-time clones (cloned by scripts/install/install_ac_simpler.sh,
# referenced by the simpler / octo / vla_policy nodesets). Never tracked
# directly — pin commits inside the install script if reproducibility is
# needed.
third_party/SimplerEnv/
third_party/ManiSkill2_real2sim/
third_party/octo/

# Former git submodules, converted to pinned install-time clones 2026-06-30.
# Cloned + pinned by scripts/install/lib/thirdparty.sh (single source of truth
# for their commit IDs), invoked from the per-env install scripts:
#   VLN-CE + habitat-lab        <- install_ac_vlnce.sh / install_ac_smartway.sh
#   Matterport3DSimulator       <- install_ac_mp3d.sh
#   lerobot + libero            <- install_ac_vla_policy.sh / install_ac_libero.sh
#                                  (public upstreams; formerly nested inside the
#                                  private vla_workspace repo, now sourced direct)
# Never tracked directly.
third_party/VLN-CE/
third_party/habitat-lab/
third_party/Matterport3DSimulator/
third_party/lerobot/
third_party/libero/

# Legacy private checkout — no longer used by any install (lerobot/libero now
# come from public upstream; openpi-client is vendored into the policy_vla
# nodeset). Ignored so a leftover local copy stays out of git; safe to
# `rm -rf third_party/vla_workspace` once the installs have been re-run.
third_party/vla_workspace/

# Personal strategy notes (not shared)
.claude/strategy-*.md

# Claude Code private dev state — public-safe sub-dirs (.claude/standard/,
# .claude/tutorials/, .claude/commands/, .claude/architect/) stay tracked.
# These four are session-local or draft-tier — never published.
.claude/plan/
.claude/log.md
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
# Auto-memory store (relocated 2026-04-29 from ~/.claude/projects/.../memory/
# via scripts/install/setup_memory_symlink.sh). Topic-routed into subdirs
# 2026-05-19 — see CLAUDE.md § Memory Layout for routing rules.
#
# Shareability is per-directory:
#   architect/     — AAS pipeline + experiment infra  (tracked)
#   platform/      — agentcanvas framework semantics  (tracked)
#   nodeset/       — specific nodeset / sim / scene   (tracked)
#   eval/          — eval-suite quirks and metric facts (tracked)
#   research/      — paper / thesis / supervisor / research-style (tracked)
#   working-style/ — general collaboration norms (local-only, NOT tracked)
#   user/          — user profile / env / prefs (local-only, NOT tracked)
#   MEMORY.md      — the index (tracked so cross-machine sync sees new entries —
#                    fixes the bug where a memory file synced via git but the
#                    index didn't, so Claude on the receiving machine couldn't
#                    find it. Append-only edits keep merge conflicts manageable.)
# Claude Code working memory — local-only, never tracked.
.claude/memory/

# Presentation slides (binary, kept out of git history)
docs/presentations/*.pptx
docs/research/presentations/*.pptx

# Scratch / reference traces — never authoritative. This also covers the doc-site
# communication-render area docs/pages/developer-guide/tmp/ — pages Claude renders
# for the user to view locally on the dev site; never tracked.
tmp/

# Architect-site large binaries — checked-out locally, kept out of git
docs/pages/aas/**/*.pdf
docs/pages/aas/adas/paper/project-page/img/ai_art.png

# Personal research content — present locally but never tracked.
# Site auto-discovers (and quietly skips) `docs/pages/research/` when absent.
docs/pages/research/

# Personal todo / planning scratchpad — present locally but never tracked.
# Site auto-discovers (and quietly skips) `docs/pages/todo/` when absent.
docs/pages/todo/

# Full-view nav/search data for the local dev site (includes gitignored
# sections). The dev server serves these in place of the committed public
# nav.json / search-index.json — see docs/_lib/_wrap_handwritten.py.
docs/assets/*.local.json

# ── Local-only maintainer files (never tracked) ─────────────────────────
# Agent instructions, working memory/overview, personal standards, and local
# tooling/scratch — present on the maintainer's machine, kept out of the repo.
CLAUDE.md
.claude/PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md
.claude/cache/
.claude/commands/research/
# Personal git-workflow commands (maintainer tooling; encode the local privacy checks).
.claude/commands/commit.md
.claude/commands/push.md
.claude/commands/pub.md
.claude/standard/blog-style.md
.claude/standard/lit-review-style.md
scripts/release/
scripts/dev/setup_memory_symlink.sh
docs/pages/developer-guide/repo/mirror.html
docs-md/versioning-draft.md
.claude/commands/architect/findings-2026-05-14-eval-noise-and-log-tracing.html
